article.headline: Army 60, American U. 55
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Jarell Brown had 19 points to lead Army in a 60-55 win over American University Wednesday. Army (12-7) hit 13-of-14 free throws in the last 1:35 to hold off and American comeback. American had a 23-17 lead at halftime, but Army opened the second half with an 11-3 run to take the lead for good, 28-26, with just over 14 minutes left. After shooting 50 percent in the first half, American hit just nine-of-31 shots in the second to finish the game at 39 percent overall. Arvydas Eitutavicius led the Eagles with 17 points, while Andre Ingram had 10 points for the Eagles (9-9). Jarell Brown had 19 points and Matt Bell had 17 points for Army, which defeated American for the first time in 12 games.
